@page "/privacy"

<PageTitle>Privacy Policy - NOSTDLIB</PageTitle>

<Navbar />

<article class="legal-page">
    <div class="container">
        <a href="/" class="back-link">&larr; Back Home</a>

        <header class="page-header">
            <span class="page-icon">🔒</span>
            <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
            <p class="page-intro">Your trust is our priority. We maintain complete confidentiality about our clients and projects.</p>
            <p class="last-updated mono">Last updated: @LastUpdated</p>
        </header>

        <section class="page-section">
            <h2>Introduction</h2>
            <p>
                NOSTDLIB ("we," "our," or "us") is committed to protecting your privacy and maintaining
                the strictest confidentiality regarding our business relationships. This Privacy Policy
                explains our commitment to discretion and how we safeguard all information related to
                our clients and projects.
            </p>
            <p>
                Confidentiality is not just a policy for us—it's a core principle of how we operate.
                We understand that our clients trust us with sensitive projects, and we take that
                responsibility seriously.
            </p>
        </section>

        <section class="page-section">
            <h2>Client Confidentiality</h2>
            <p>
                We maintain complete confidentiality regarding all aspects of our client relationships.
                This means:
            </p>
            <ul class="privacy-list">
                <li><strong>No Client Disclosure:</strong> We never reveal which companies or individuals we work with, whether past, present, or future clients.</li>
                <li><strong>No Project Details:</strong> We do not share any information about the nature, scope, or specifics of work performed for our clients.</li>
                <li><strong>No Public References:</strong> We do not use client names, logos, or project descriptions in our marketing materials without explicit written consent.</li>
                <li><strong>No Third-Party Sharing:</strong> Information about our business relationships is never shared with third parties under any circumstances.</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <section class="page-section">
            <h2>Why We Keep Things Private</h2>
            <p>
                Our commitment to confidentiality stems from our understanding that:
            </p>
            <ul class="privacy-list">
                <li>Your business strategies and technical decisions are proprietary information</li>
                <li>Knowledge of vendor relationships can be competitively sensitive</li>
                <li>Project details may involve trade secrets or intellectual property</li>
                <li>Trust is the foundation of any successful professional partnership</li>
            </ul>
            <p>
                When you work with NOSTDLIB, you can be confident that your engagement with us
                remains strictly between us.
            </p>
        </section>

        <section class="page-section">
            <h2>Our Commitment</h2>
            <p>
                All team members at NOSTDLIB are bound by strict confidentiality agreements.
                We maintain this commitment:
            </p>
            <ul class="privacy-list">
                <li>During active engagements</li>
                <li>After project completion</li>
                <li>Indefinitely, unless you explicitly authorize disclosure</li>
            </ul>
            <p>
                This policy applies to all forms of communication—verbal, written, and digital.
                We will never confirm or deny any business relationship without your prior written consent.
            </p>
        </section>

        <section class="page-section">
            <h2>Changes to This Policy</h2>
            <p>
                We may update this privacy policy from time to time. We will notify you of any changes
                by posting the new privacy policy on this page and updating the "Last updated" date.
                Your continued use of our services after any changes indicates your acceptance of
                the updated policy.
            </p>
        </section>

        <section class="page-section page-footer">
            <h2>Contact Us</h2>
            <p>If you have questions about this privacy policy or our practices, please contact us.</p>
            <a href="/#contact" class="btn btn-primary">Contact Us</a>
        </section>
    </div>
</article>

<Footer />

@code {
    private string LastUpdated => DateTime.Now.ToString("MMMM yyyy");
}